{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17632141","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17632141"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:36:54+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:36:54+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17419"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17419","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17419"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10109"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70558"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10109","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10109"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17419"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56022"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5502"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23682"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23686"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70558","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/70558"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Transtheoretical Model is widely used to understand how people change health-related behaviours, such as smoking cessation or increasing physical activity. This model describes distinct stages that individuals move through when making behavioural changes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes an individual in the contemplation stage of behaviour change?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Has no intention to change behaviour","Has maintained the changed behaviour for over six months","Is actively engaging in the new behaviour","Has started making small behavioural modifications","Is aware of the problem and considering change within six months"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Econtemplation stage\u003C/strong\u003E is characterised by awareness of problematic behaviour and intention to change within the next six months. During this stage, individuals weigh the pros and cons of changing their behaviour but have not yet committed to taking action.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options represent other stages of change:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHas no intention to change behaviour\u003C/strong\u003E describes the precontemplation stage, where individuals are unaware or unwilling to acknowledge problematic behaviour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHas maintained the changed behaviour for over six months\u003C/strong\u003E describes the maintenance stage, where individuals work to prevent relapse.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIs actively engaging in the new behaviour\u003C/strong\u003E describes the action stage, where individuals have made specific modifications to their behaviour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHas started making small behavioural modifications\u003C/strong\u003E describes the preparation stage, where individuals are getting ready to take action within 30 days.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding these stages helps healthcare providers tailor interventions appropriately to support successful behaviour change.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The Transtheoretical Model describes five stages of behaviour change: precontemplation, contemplation, preparation, action, and maintenance.","The contemplation stage is characterised by awareness of a problem and intention to change within 6 months.","Moving from contemplation to preparation requires development of a specific plan for change."],"references":["Shultz JM, Sullivan LM, Galea S. Public Health: An Introduction to the Science and Practice of Population Health. Springer Publishing Company; 2021."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56022"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17419"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56022","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56022"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-15T19:17:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-04T00:09:32+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10109"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70558"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"5326","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/